{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/96963", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/96963/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/96963/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/96963/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/96963", "id": 1233505974, "node_id": "I_kwDOAAsO6M5Jhc62", "number": 96963, "title": "Suggestion: Provide FloorEntry and CeilEntry method for BTreeMap and BTreeSet ", "user": {"login": "Ai-Zixun", "id": 6028835, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjYwMjg4MzU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6028835?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun", "html_url": "https://github.com/Ai-Zixun", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 4, "created_at": "2022-05-12T06:28:34Z", "updated_at": "2022-05-15T02:14:19Z", "closed_at": "2022-05-15T02:14:18Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I am wondering if the Rust core team has any plan to add `FloorEntry` and `CeilEntry` to the rust `BTreeMap` and `BTreeSet` in the standard library? \r\n\r\nComing from Java, I found that both the `FloorEntry` and `CeilEntry` in the `NavigableMap<K, V> `interface in the Java standard library when using a sorted map/set.\r\n\r\n* FloorEntry: Returns a key-value mapping associated with the greatest key less than or equal to the given key, or null if there is no such key.\r\n* CeilEntry: Returns a key-value mapping associated with the least key greater than or equal to the given key, or null if there is no such key.  \r\n\r\nIn rust, we can use `range<T, R>` to create a `Range<'_, T>` that implements the `core::iter::traits::double_ended::DoubleEndedIterator` trait to get the Floor Entry and the Ceil Entry. Nevertheless, that seems to be a more costly approach than traversing the sorted B-Tree to get the corresponding entries directly in O(B * log(N)) time.\r\n\r\nWe can get the floor and the ceil entries with the following code in rust: \r\n * FloorEntry: `map.range(..=key).next_back().unwrap();`\r\n* CeilEntry: `map.range(key..).next().unwrap();`", "closed_by": {"login": "Ai-Zixun", "id": 6028835, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjYwMjg4MzU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6028835?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun", "html_url": "https://github.com/Ai-Zixun", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Ai-Zixun/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "